			<p><add>Yiddish</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><sic><addressee>Rev. Isack Leeser</addressee></sic></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p><add>Something is written with pencil sideways on the right side of the page in Yiddish</add></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><add>Yiddish</add></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>&#44; Wed. day before</p> 
          <p rend="align(right)"><date>Rosh Hodesh Nissan &#40;April&#41;<lb/>1851</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>&#44; <placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I hereby let you know that I<lb/> have sold the three prayer&#45;books of<lb/> Ashkenazic &#38; Polish ritual&#44; as well as the<lb/> three Pentateuchs. Please write to me what<lb/> to do with your money&#44; and send me<lb/> again 6 prayer&#45;books of Ashkenazic<lb/> ritual. You might also send one set<lb/> holiday&#45;books of Sephardic ritual with<lb/> translation&#44; if that does not inconvenience<lb/> you too much and if they are not of<lb/> too high a price. Send them to me<lb/> at the lowest price.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">With respect&#44; and wishes for a<lb/> happy holiday&#44; Your friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">N. Ottinger</persName></p>
			<p>I should also like one prayer&#45;book in<lb/> gilt binding&#44; at lowest price.</p>
          
        </body>
